# Cursor Agent Rules

At the start of each new session or task, read PROJECT.md and
DECISIONS.md before doing anything else. These are your source of
truth for what this project is and decisions that have been made.

## How to use them
- PROJECT.md tells you what we're building and why. If a proposed
  solution conflicts with the goals there, flag it rather than
  working around it.
- DECISIONS.md tells you what has already been decided. Don't
  relitigate these. If a new task requires revisiting a decision,
  say so explicitly rather than quietly changing things.

## General behavior
- Simple is good. Over-orchestrated is bad. Clever is fine when
  it earns its complexity.
- A small patch is often the right fix. But if debugging is
  compounding, the patch is probably wrong - propose a fresh
  approach instead.
- When scope or approach is unclear, ask.
- Don't modify working code that isn't related to the current task.
- This is a portfolio project. Code will be read by engineers.
  Prefer clarity over brevity - name things well, keep functions
  focused, avoid clever shortcuts that obscure intent.  No emojis anywhere.
- Never hardcode secrets or API keys. Always use environment variables.
- Never use em dashes (--) in any generated text or code comments.
  Use a regular dash (-) or reword the sentence instead.

